<h2 id="nav-disabling">
    <a href="#nav-grouping">#</a> Grouping fields
</h2>
<p>Use class <code>.fieldset-group</code> for grouping sets of fields and display them inline.</p>

<div class="code-example">
    <div>
        <form data-clone>
            <div class="fieldset-group fieldset-group--sticked">
                <label>Search website:</label>
                <input type="text" placeholder="Enter search phrase">
                <button class="btn">
                    <span class="icon icon-search"></span>
                </button>
            </div>
        </form>
    </div>

    <pre lang="html"></pre>
</div>

<h2 id="nav-disabling">
    <a href="#nav-disabling">#</a> Disabling fields
</h2>
<p>Use <code>disabled</code> attribute on tag <code>fieldset</code> to disable group of fields.</p>
<p>To disable single elements just do it in classic way by using attribute <code>readonly</code> or <code>disabled</code></p>

<div class="code-example">
    <div>
        <form data-clone>
            <div class="row">
                <label>Text field</label>
                <input type="text" placeholder="First name" disabled>
            </div>

            <fieldset disabled>
                <p class="legend">Disabled specific field</p>

                <div class="row">
                    <label>
                        <input type="checkbox" checked>
                        Checkbox 1
                    </label>
                </div>

                <div class="row">
                    <label>
                        <input type="checkbox">
                        Checkbox 2
                    </label>
                </div>

                <div class="row">
                    <label>
                        <input type="checkbox">
                        Checkbox 3
                    </label>
                </div>
            </fieldset>
        </form>
    </div>

    <pre lang="html"></pre>
</div>

